Ctrl + Shift + B => run script in python
F5 => run script with input function
exit () => exits python

indentation in python refers to a block of code; not just for readability like
in other programs

install python
install atom
install hydrogen package
install atom python runlines
install atom python run (shortcut enabled ctrl + shift + b)



Then, install the following so that hydrogen can run code just like jupyter for data science

forpython -m pip install ipykernel
pip install pip==22.0.4
python -m ipykernel install --user
# install plot library
pip install matplotlib
pip install sklearn
pip install pydotplus
for graphviz install from official site, do not initiate pip install graphviz, download 64 bit version
when prompted, add path to current user.
